<BaseLayout title="About me" pathname="/about/">
  <div class="about">
    <div class="about-header">
      <h1>About me</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="about-section">
      <p>I’m a UX engineer living and working remotely in San Marcos, Texas.</p>
      <p>
        I focus on design systems and front-end architecture, improving consistency, reducing duplication, and speeding up design-to-development workflows. I work across design and code, building
        high-fidelity prototypes that map directly to production interfaces and <a href="https://github.com/edelstone">open-source UI tools</a>.
      </p>
      <p>I use AI to accelerate prototyping, generate components, and shorten iteration cycles, freeing more time for refinement, testing, and product thinking.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Tools</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Design:</strong> Figma, Balsamiq, paper and pencil</li>
      <li><strong>Code:</strong> HTML, CSS, React, Git, static site generators, UI component libraries</li>
      <li><strong>AI:</strong> Figma Make, ChatGPT, Copilot</li>
      <li><strong>Research:</strong> UserTesting, Google Analytics, customer interviews</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Interests</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Film:</strong> Big fan of ’80s Hollywood, Christmas comedies, and over-the-top action flicks.</li>
      <li><strong>TV:</strong> My favorite shows include <em>Slings &amp; Arrows</em>, <em>Community</em>, and <em>The IT Crowd</em>.</li>
      <li><strong>Books:</strong> I read the occasional fiction classic, but otherwise I’m into non-fiction, particularly on the subjects of space science and U.S. history.</li>
      <li><strong>Music:</strong> I try to listen to new music every day. <a href="http://www.last.fm/user/tsanzer">My stats are on Last.fm</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Podcasts:</strong> I usually listen to a couple podcasts a day. Lately I’m enjoying <em>Dad Saves America</em> and <em>The Winston Marshall Show</em>.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Real world:</strong> Bicycles, solo hiking, cooking, photography, minimalism, Texas barbecue, telescopes, <a
          href="https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/edit?mid=18UmsEMmCnD-Nw_pzG3fmYnuURfY&usp=sharing">National Parks</a
        >, and road trips.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Life goal:</strong> One day I hope to be recruited by an intergalactic team of fighter pilots like Alex Rogan in <em>The Last Starfighter</em>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
